name: Google Assistant
description:
• WHAT IS IT
Actions on Google and Google Assistant are one of the major Google technical areas and we want to invite the whole developer community to learn about creating Actions for the Google Assistant.

“Build Actions for Your Community” is an open and modular event series designed by Google and offered to communities worldwide. We're offering opportunities to developers attending the event to learn how to build Actions for the Google Assistant that are useful for their community - whether it's a professional network, interest group, or your hometown. This way, you can build something in an area that you care about or are interested in

name: JavaScript Workshop
description:
Javascript workshop

The purpose of this workshop is to introduce modern javascript for the students who may or may not know about javascript, to show them the power of this programming language, by beginning with a small introduction, then discussing and reviewing some of the trending javascript frameworks, ending the workshop with coding simple one or two apps.

Agenda

11:00 - 11:30 _ Registration
11:30 - 12:00 _ Introduction ( What is javascript , why to use it, what it can do )
12:00 - 12:30 ( introducing frameworks - React, Angular, Vue )
12:30 - 12:50 ( coffee break )
1:00 - 2:30 ( coding )
2:30- 3:30 ( coding challenge )
